			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Polyglycerol fatty acid esters (PGFEs) are a type of biocompatible hydrophilic polyether polyol. They are considered as potential alternatives to polyethylene glycol in modifying nanomedicines. PGFEs are produced by the polymerization of glycerol in the presence of an alkaline catalyst followed by esterification with fatty acids. They are used in the food industry as emulsifiers, stabilizers, and texturizers, improving the texture, shelf life, and stability of food products.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">聚甘油脂肪酸酯（PGFEs）是一种生物相容性亲水聚醚多元醇。在纳米药物改性方面，它们被认为是聚乙二醇的潜在替代品。PGFEs 由甘油在碱性催化剂作用下聚合而成，然后与脂肪酸酯化。它们在食品工业中用作乳化剂、稳定剂和质构剂，可改善食品的质地、保质期和稳定性。</common:generalComment>
